{
  "doc_id": "10683",
  "text": "TNF-a inhibitors improve insulin sensitivity in patients with inflammatory conditions [CITATION_1] . A retrospective cohort study of rheumatoid arthritis and psoriasis patients found that TNF inhibitors reduced incident T2D, with a hazard ratio of 0.62, compared to non-biologic disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs [CITATION_2] . Another retrospective study found that anti-TNF agents with concomitant hydroxychloroquine use conferred lower diabetes risk, but not when anti-TNF treatment was used without hydroxychloroquine [CITATION_3] .",
